    <w:p><w:pPr><w:spacing w:line="240"/></w:pPr></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading3"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:b/><w:t>Wells Fargo — New York, NY</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    <w:p><w:r><w:t>Senior Automation Engineer | January 2023 – December 2025</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:ind w:left="720"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>• Architected enterprise-grade multi-layered automation frameworks using Cucumber (BDD), QAFBDD, Java, Selenium, Playwright, and TestNG with Gradle, enabling parallel execution and reducing regression test cycle time by 40%</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:ind w:left="720"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>• Engineered comprehensive backend validation pipelines using SQL and Postman across distributed microservices, ensuring data consistency and business logic accuracy in payment processing workflows</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:ind w:left="720"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>• Executed parallel and cross-browser test suites via Jenkins and Vulcan across multiple environments, improving defect detection rate and reducing time-to-production by 35%</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:ind w:left="720"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>• Developed full-stack components using C#, .NET MVC, and Entity Framework for Web, Console, and Windows Service applications; integrated test automation with deployment pipelines</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:ind w:left="720"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>• Managed ServiceNow Change Requests for production deployments; optimized and maintained AutoSys jobs for recurring batch processing and reconciliation workflows</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:ind w:left="720"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>• Investigated production defects leveraging AppDynamics, Splunk, and BigPanda monitoring tools; maintained robust CI/CD pipelines via GitHub Actions, Jenkins, UCD, and Harness</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:ind w:left="720"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>• Mentored junior QA engineers on automation best practices, framework design patterns, and continuous integration methodologies</w:t></w:r></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:spacing w:line="240"/></w:pPr></w:p>
    
    <w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading3"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:b/><w:t>FISERV — Berkeley Heights, NJ</w:t></w:r></w:p>
